---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Documentation · Nevermind">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <h1>Documentation</h1>
    <p>Everything you need to install Nevermind, connect your account, and use the API.</p>
  </section>

  <div class="docs-layout">
    <nav class="docs-sidebar" aria-label="Docs navigation">
      <span class="docs-sidebar__section">Overview</span>
      <a href="#getting-started">Getting started</a>
      <a href="#installation">Installation</a>
      <a href="#sign-in">Sign in &amp; connect</a>

      <span class="docs-sidebar__section">API</span>
      <a href="#api-auth">Authentication</a>
      <a href="#chat-completions">Chat completions</a>
      <a href="#models">Models</a>

      <span class="docs-sidebar__section">Reference</span>
      <a href="#credits-limits">Credits &amp; limits</a>
      <a href="#errors">Error codes</a>
      <a href="#device-auth">Device authorization</a>

      <span class="docs-sidebar__section">Account</span>
      <a href="#account-billing">Account &amp; billing</a>
    </nav>

    <article class="docs-article">
      <h2 id="getting-started">Getting started</h2>
      <p>Nevermind is an AI-native desktop command palette. Press <code>Alt+Space</code>, type what you want, and get instant actions. The desktop app also includes an AI builder that creates custom extensions from natural language descriptions.</p>

      <h3 id="installation">Installation</h3>
      <p>Download the latest version from <a href="https://github.com/pablopunk/nvm/releases">GitHub Releases</a>. Choose your platform:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>macOS</strong> — <code>.zip</code> for Apple Silicon or Intel</li>
        <li><strong>Windows</strong> — <code>.exe</code> installer or portable</li>
        <li><strong>Linux</strong> — <code>.AppImage</code> or <code>.deb</code></li>
      </ul>

      <h3 id="sign-in">Sign in &amp; connect</h3>
      <p>Open the palette (<code>Alt+Space</code>), type "Log in to Nevermind", and follow the browser prompt to authenticate. Once signed in, the app uses your Nevermind account for AI features and model access.</p>
      <p>The app supports a <code>nvm://</code> protocol handler for one-click sign-in from the dashboard. If the protocol handler is unavailable, you can paste a device code manually from the app's sign-in flow.</p>

      <hr />

      <h2 id="api-auth">API Authentication</h2>
      <p>Nevermind provides an OpenAI-compatible chat completions API. Authenticate using a Personal Access Token (PAT) created from your <a href="/profile">profile page</a>.</p>
      <p>Pass the token as a Bearer header:</p>
      <pre><code>Authorization: Bearer nvm_pat_YOUR_TOKEN</code></pre>
      <p>Tokens are prefixed with <code>nvm_pat_</code> and can be revoked individually from the dashboard. Never share a token or commit it to version control.</p>

      <h3 id="chat-completions">Chat completions</h3>
      <p>
        <span class="api-method api-method--post">POST</span>
        <span class="endpoint">https://api.nvm.fyi/api/v1/chat/completions</span>
      </p>
      <p>Accepts standard OpenAI Chat Completions request bodies. Models are selected automatically based on availability and routing configuration.</p>
      <pre><code>curl -sS https://api.nvm.fyi/api/v1/chat/completions \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer nvm_pat_YOUR_TOKEN" \
  -d '&#123;
    "model": "nevermind",
    "messages": [
      &#123;"role": "user", "content": "Explain how credits work"&#125;
    ]
  &#125;'</code></pre>

      <h3 id="models">Models</h3>
      <p>Nevermind routes requests across a pool of supported AI providers. The model you choose determines the provider path and capabilities. Model availability depends on your plan and the current backend configuration.</p>
      <p>To discover the currently active model, the desktop app queries <span class="endpoint">GET /api/v1/active-model</span> after authentication. The response includes the model ID, context window size, and supported input types.</p>

      <hr />

      <h2 id="credits-limits">Credits &amp; limits</h2>
      <p>Every account includes free monthly credits. Paid plans add additional credits per billing cycle. See the <a href="/pricing">pricing page</a> for current plans and FAQ.</p>
      <p>Rate limits depend on your plan. When you hit a limit, the API returns a <code>429</code> status with a <code>Retry-After</code> header.</p>

      <h3 id="errors">Error codes</h3>
      <table class="table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Status</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>200</code></td><td>Success — request completed normally</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>401</code></td><td>Missing, invalid, or revoked PAT</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>402</code></td><td>Insufficient credits — add credits or wait for monthly reset</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>403</code></td><td>Forbidden — cross-origin request rejected</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>426</code></td><td>Update required — your desktop app version is unsupported</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>429</code></td><td>Rate limited — wait and retry after the Retry-After window</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>503</code></td><td>Service unavailable — backend maintenance or overload</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <hr />

      <h2 id="device-auth">Device authorization</h2>
      <p>The desktop app authenticates using a device authorization flow. The app requests a short-lived code, opens a browser verification URL for approval, and polls for a token exchange.</p>
      <p>When using the <a href="/profile">Connect desktop app</a> feature from the dashboard, the <code>nvm://</code> deep link carries only the device code — never a PAT. If the protocol handler fails to open (common on sandboxed Linux browsers), a manual code copy fallback is shown.</p>

      <h3 id="account-billing">Account &amp; billing</h3>
      <p>Manage your subscription, view balances, and create API tokens from the <a href="/profile">profile dashboard</a>. Billing is handled securely by Stripe — Nevermind does not store payment details.</p>
      <p>The <a href="/profile#connect-desktop">Connect desktop app</a> panel on the profile page generates a short-lived device code you can use to sign into the desktop app with one click.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
